  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - ROGUE</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>DUELING WITH THE MOUSE</font> - <small>Anonymous , Prexus</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>Rogues are known as poor duelers, and that is mostly because of their relative lack of HP and AC to the melee classes, which also makes them easy for casters to beat too.  What many people have never seen is a truly great rogue
dueler.  As many people don't know, Rogues are the best melee damage dealers, when we are facing the backside of our opponent.  When facing the front side, however, much is left to be desired.  There are several
techniques you can use to make it easier to get behind your opponent.  The first is to simply be hidden before the duel starts.  Unless your opponent has see invisible, you get a free backstab, and against non pet casters the fight often ends quickly from there with our rapid fire attacks. The second technique is circle strafing. Using (commonly found in FPS games) WASD controls for movement, and have mouselook on.  To circle strafe, activate mouselook by holding down the right mouse button, and this will make the turn left and right movement keys become strafe keys.  You can now circle around your opponent with ease.  While doing this, jump over them and turn around quickly, and you can often get a backstab in.  Also, they will often lose attacks on you because you are bouncing around all over the place, and they can't point towards you to hit them.<br>
<p>Now for ways to duel specific classes:<br>
Bards - Stay away! They have songs that will unhide you, other songs that will hurt you, and they are too fast to get near the whole time.  If they decide to melee you, you stand a good chance but their songs can heal them fast enough to help
confenscate for your higher damage output.</p>
<P>
Warriors - Try to step back and hide a lot, they have no way of un-hiding you and you can usually get a couple free attacks in after a backstab as they turn around.  Also jump over them, and do anything else possible to keep them from hitting you.<P>
Pet casters - Another no-no.  I have honestly not figured out a way to take one on other then hiding and sneaking away
until a mob has them at low health or their pet busy, then attacking them.  It isn't fair to them but we aren't exactly the kind of people that would be considered fair.
<P>
Wizards - Run in and hack them to death!  Just run up to them and hope they don't root you, then shred them with low delay weapons.  These duels are usually over very quickly.  MR is a good thing.
<P>
Hybrids - Hybrids can be doable. Don't even think of dueling a paladin unless you know he
doesn't use mouselook and has a slow computer.  Their lay on hands effectively gives them 2 lives.  Shadow Knights can also be nasty with HT but it is not quite as bad.  Both can blind you, SKs can fear you, so wear high MR armor if possible.  Rangers are probably the easiest of the hybrids
until 39 (sow), they have similar HP and slightly better AC with some minor buffs, but we have backstab and lots of damage output.  As with the warrior try and confuse him by running circles around him while attacking, and hiding when you can.
<P>

While rogues are far from a great dueling class it can be done.  Try to avoid letting your opponent let you know you are a rogue, if you are going to duel someone try and make them think you are a warrior by holding some 1hs weapons in your hand, when you hide on them then backstab them it will surprise them a lot more, and the chance that they have see invisible memorized is much less
. I have managed to win some duels and loose many, but I have learned a lot in the process, winning more lately then losing.</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>&nbsp;</td></tr>
